   <body>
      <p>The Qualifications and Benefits feature allows you to provide benefits at the bundle level for a set of products or categories. Bundles are a set of products grouped together and sold at a parent level, but not at the individual product level. For more information about Tiered and Non-tiered qualifications and benefits, refer to the <xref href="../qualifications_and_benefi_102432700/102432700.xml"
               format="dita">Qualifications and Benefits</xref> section.</p>
      <p>
         <fig>
            <image placement="break"
                   width="700"
                   href="../attachments/102432712/107118620.jpg"/>
         </fig>
      </p>
      <p>The following table describes the actions you can take on the Qualifications and Benefits page:</p>
      <p>
         <table>
            <tgroup cols="2">
               <colspec colname="col1"/>
               <colspec colname="col2"/>
               <thead>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Fields</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Description</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </thead>
               <tbody>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Bundle Name</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Select the bundle name for the set of products you want to buy.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Product Name</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Add products or categories in the Product Name column. For adding products or categories, please refer to the <xref href="../adding-products_102432695_102432695/102432695_1.xml"
                                 format="dita">Adding Products</xref> section. Products are the list of products which are purchased by customers at the bundle level.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>UOM (Unit Of Measures)</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>It defaults to Each.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Type</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Auto-populated based on the products or categories selected.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Unit</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Enter the unit of the product.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Unit Price</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Enter the price of the product.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Extended Price</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Auto-calculated price for the whole unit of the product.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Bundle Price</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Aggregated price of the products that are grouped in the bundle.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Save</p>
                     </entry>
                     <entry>
                        <p>Saves the changes.</p>
                     </entry>
                  </row>
               </tbody>
            </tgroup>
         </table>
      </p>
